    "content": "Somali Interior Minister Ali Yusuf Ali, widely known as Cali Xoosh, has publicly refuted claims that he has resigned from his position. In a statement issued on Wednesday, the minister dismissed the reports as false and urged the public to disregard them.\n\nThe rumors had circulated on social media earlier this week, prompting the minister to clarify his status. Xoosh reiterated that he remains fully engaged in his duties as Minister of Interior, Federal Affairs, and Reconciliation.\n\nThis is not the first time such rumors have emerged. Political figures in Somalia often face speculation about resignations during periods of political tension or leadership transitions. Xoosh has been a key figure in the federal government, overseeing internal security and reconciliation efforts.\n\nFor the Somali diaspora, stability within the interior ministry is crucial as it handles matters related to citizenship, diaspora engagement, and internal security. False reports of resignations can create unnecessary uncertainty among Somalis abroad who follow political developments closely.\n\nThe minister's denial has been welcomed by many who view him as a stabilizing force. Observers note that the swift clarification helps maintain confidence in the government's continuity.\n\nRead the original report from Horseed Media here: https://horseedmedia.net/cali-xoosh-oo-beeniyey-inuu-iskacasilayo-xilka-wasiirka-arrimaha-gudaha/424021/",
